					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">What you describe is sometimes called <em>dynamic channel allocation</em>, basically presenting <em>virtual</em> channels which are mapped dynamically to physical channels, allowing previous notes to decay after new ones are started. The Namco 106 sound chip adds 8 identical wave-table channels to the NES, plenty for what you describe.</div>

